  "prompt": "What is the exact difference between supercharger & turbocharger?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between superchargers and turbochargers:\n\nSupercharger:\n1. Powered directly by engine's crankshaft via a belt or gear\n2. Provides immediate power boost\n3. Consistent power delivery\n4. Increases engine load slightly\n5. Simpler design\n6. Less fuel-efficient\n7. Generally less complex to install\n8. Operates at lower maximum boost pressures\n\nTurbocharger:\n1. Powered by exhaust gases\n2. Slight turbo lag before boost kicks in\n3. Power delivery is less linear\n4. No direct engine load increase\n5. More complex design\n6. More fuel-efficient\n7. More complicated installation\n8. Can achieve higher boost pressures\n9. Typically more efficient at higher RPMs\n\nSimilarities:\n- Both increase engine power\n- Both compress intake air\n- Both enhance engine performance\n- Both used in performance and racing applications\n\nThe choice between supercharger and turbocharger depends on specific performance requirements, vehicle type, and desired characteristics.",
